<taxonomicName authorityName="Lyman" authorityYear="1861" box="[751,960,152,179]" class="Ophiuroidea" family="Ophiotrichidae" genus="Macrophiothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ophiurida" pageId="12" pageNumber="89" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="subSpecies" species="hirsuta" subSpecies="cheneyi">
<emphasis box="[751,774,153,178]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="89">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[789,960,152,178]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="89">hirsuta cheneyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because on their photo, the arms are only 10 times as long as the disc diameter.
</paragraph>
